Observation Details: *rare. Thanks to Charles Morano for putting me on this bird.  Recorded male song and juvenile begging calls. Witnessed feeding one fledgling. Confirmed breeding at this location.

The first bird of the day! I heard it as soon as I arrived at the parking lot--a singing blue-winged warbler! He seemed alarmed by something and was giving an alarm call which I recorded. I was able to get great looks of him and take some photographs that I hope turn out. Seen along the trail where small trees create a thick corridor from pastures. interestingly, Merlin identified the sharp alarm call as a northern cardinal. A cardinal did appear, trying to figure out what the ruckus was about later as did a surprise pine warbler! The pine warbler was another target for this morning! And I've already seen two targets just by the parking lot!
